PLACEHOLDER — Binary DOCX template lives in @borjie/document-templates.

The actual `template.docx` is a Carbone Universal Templating Language
document maintained in a separate, binary-friendly package:

  packages/document-templates/monthly-owner-report/template.docx

That package versions templates independently and is pulled in by
tenants via pnpm. This placeholder exists so the runtime template
loader has a stable filesystem path to fall back on while the binary
asset is sourced separately.

Carbone template tags expected (see ./data-schema.ts for full Zod shape):

  {d.period.start}            ISO date — period start
  {d.period.end}              ISO date — period end
  {d.property.name}           string  — property display name
  {d.property.address}        string  — property street address
  {d.owner.name}              string  — owner full name
  {d.owner.currencyPref}      string  — ISO-4217 currency code preferred by owner
  {d.summary.rentCollected}   number  — gross rent collected in owner currency
  {d.summary.expenses}        number  — total expenses
  {d.summary.netOwner}        number  — net amount due to owner
  {d.units[i].unitNumber}     string  — per-unit ledger rows
  {d.units[i].tenantName}     string
  {d.units[i].rentDue}        number
  {d.units[i].rentPaid}       number
  {d.narrative}               markdown — AI-synthesised executive summary
  {d.citations[i].id}         per-claim citation marker
  {d.citations[i].claim}      claim text
  {d.citations[i].source.ref} source ref (ledger row, message id, etc.)
